Wt is python?
==========

	Ã˜ It is a high-level , interpreted, general-purpose programming lng
	Ã˜ Python has simplicity, readability and rapid development 
	Ã˜ It was designed so that humans  can read n write code easily.

Who developed python?
=================

	Ã˜ Python was created by Guido van Rossum
	Ã˜ First release in 1991
	Ã˜ Named after monty python , not the snake


Why python is popular?
=================

	Ã˜ Easy to learn
	Ã˜ Simple english like syntax
	Ã˜ Less code compared to other langs
	Ã˜ Huge community support
	Ã˜ Massive library ecosystem
	Ã˜ Work on all OS


Where python is used?
================

	Ã˜ Web development 
	Ã˜ Automation & scripting 
	Ã˜ DevOps & cloud computing 
	Ã˜ Data science & analytics 
	Ã˜ AI & ML
	Ã˜ Cyber security
	Ã˜ Game development 

Features of python 
=============

	1. Simple & Readable :- no curly  braces {}, uses indentation 
	2. Interpreted language:- code is executed line by line , no compilation step
	3. Dynamically typed:- no need to declare data types explicitly 
	4. Platform independent:- same code runs on w-os, linux-os and macos
	5. Open source :- free to use and distribute 

Python language levels
=================

	1. Low level:- close to hardware 
	2. High-level :- human-readable

Python versions
============

	Ã˜ Python 2 :- deprecated 
	Ã˜ Python 3 :- current & recommended 
	Ã˜ Always use python 3

Python execution model
==================

	1. Write python code (.py)
	2. Python interpreter reads the code
	3. Code is converted into bytecode
	4. Bytecode is executed by python vm
	5. Output is produced 

Wt is an interpreter?
===============

	Ã˜ Executes code line by line
	Ã˜ Stops execution if any error occurs 
	Ã˜ Helps in easy debugging

Python keywords 
============

	Ã˜ Keywords are reserved words that have special meaning

