Identifiers in python 
===============

	Ã˜ Identifiers are names  used to identify :- variables, functions and classes

Rules:- 
======

	Ã˜ Must start with a letter or _
	Ã˜ Can not start with a number 
	Ã˜ Can not use special characters expect _
	Ã˜ Case-sensitive

Python indentation 
==============

	Ã˜ Python uses indentation instead of curly braces {}
	Ã˜ Indentation defines code blocks
	Ã˜ Incorrect indentation causes errors
	Ã˜ This makes python code clean and readable 

Comments in python 
===============

Comments are used to ðŸ‘‡

	Ã˜ Explain code
	Ã˜ Improve readability

Types
=====

	Ã˜ Single line : # <comment>
	Ã˜ Multi-line: """ <comment> """

